cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a learning algorithm for auto-encoders based on a rate-distortion objective, which is a common topic in machine learning and specifically in deep learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of a measure of entropy, which is a topic in information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely category as well. The experiments involve using over-complete bases, which is a common technique in computer vision, suggesting cs.CV (Computer Vision) as another possible category. The paper also discusses the use of regularization, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category. Finally, the paper proposes a learning algorithm, which is a common topic in neural networks, suggesting cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible category.
